a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = root 3 13"
shows  "x powr 6 = 169"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $(\sqrt[3]{13})^6$. The final Answer is 169
 ### Proof
 We have $$(\sqrt[3]{13})^6 = (13^{1/3})^6 = 13^{\frac{1}{3}\cdot 6} = 13^2 = \boxed{169}.$$
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = root 3 13"
shows  "x powr 6 = 169"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the sixth power of the cube root of 13. The final answer is 169.
